---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { social } from '../data/site';
const email = social.email || 'hello@jaindisha.in';
---

<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy"
  updated="10 June 2026"
  description="How Disha Jain collects, uses and protects your personal data on jaindisha.in."
>
  <p class="note">
    This policy is written to align with India's Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023.
  </p>

  <p>
    This policy explains what personal data I collect when you use <strong>jaindisha.in</strong> or
    book a session, and how I use and protect it. I am the data fiduciary: <strong>Disha Jain</strong>,
    Dehradun, India.
  </p>

  <h2>What I collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Booking details</strong>: your name, email, phone number, and anything you choose to share in the intake form.</li>
    <li><strong>Session information</strong>: brief notes I keep to support our work together.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment information</strong>: handled by my payment provider. I receive a confirmation and reference, not your full card or bank details.</li>
    <li><strong>Basic technical data</strong>: standard logs and, if enabled, privacy-friendly analytics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How I use it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To schedule, hold and deliver your sessions.</li>
    <li>To communicate with you about your bookings.</li>
    <li>To take payment and issue confirmations.</li>
    <li>To meet legal and ethical record-keeping obligations.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>I do not sell your data, and I do not use it for advertising.</p>

  <h2>Who processes your data</h2>
  <p>A few trusted services help run the practice. Each handles only what it needs:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Razorpay</strong> for payments.</li>
    <li><strong>Cal.com</strong> for scheduling.</li>
    <li><strong>Google Firebase</strong> for secure booking storage.</li>
    <li><strong>Netlify</strong> for hosting the website.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
  <p>
    What you share in sessions is treated as confidential, within the ethical and legal limits I
    explain at the start of our work (for example, where there is a serious risk of harm).
  </p>

  <h2>Storage, retention and security</h2>
  <p>
    Your data is stored securely with access limited to me. I keep records for 10 years to meet
    ethical and legal record-keeping obligations, then securely delete them.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You can ask to access, correct or delete your personal data, or withdraw consent, by emailing
    me. I will respond within a reasonable time.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    Minors are welcome with a parent or guardian's involvement. For anyone under 18, a parent or
    guardian gives consent and is present for sessions, and may exercise the data rights above on
    the minor's behalf.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any privacy question or request, email <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>
